Prevent CurlMultiConnection from over-riding curl options

Previously, the CurlMultiConnection would over-write the HTTP
GET method with POST if there was a request body.  This is incorrect behavior.
This patch removes that limitation.

It also adds a provision to allow completely arbitrary HTTP method defined
by the user, regardless of what the underlying Endpoint is supposed to use.
This can be enabled using curlOpts globally:

```
$params = array();
$params['connectionParams']['curlOpts'] = array(
   CURLOPT_CUSTOMREQUEST => "PATCH"
);
$client = new Elasticsearch\Client($params);
```

Which will change *all* HTTP methods to the configured method.  Or it can be done per-request:

```
$client = new Elasticsearch\Client();

$params = array(
  'index' => 'my_index',
  'type' => 'type',
  'body' => array( 'match_all' => array() ),
  'curlOpts' => array(
    CURLOPT_CUSTOMREQUEST => "PATCH"
  )
);
$response = $client->search($params);
```

